Chennai Beats Bangalore for Second Indian Premier League Title

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-05-28T18:14:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-28/chennai-beats-bangalore-for-second-indian-premier-league-title.html
The Chennai Super Kings beat Royal
Challengers Bangalore by 58 runs to win their second straight
Indian Premier League cricket title.  Murali Vijay scored 95 runs from 52 balls as Chennai
reached 205-5 in its 20 overs.  Michael Hussey  had 63 and paired
with Vijay for an opening 159.  Ravchandran Ashwin then took 3-16 as Bangalore was reduced
to 147-8 in response. Saurabh Tiwary top-scored for Bangalore
with 42.  Chennai, which defeated the Mumbai Indians for last year’s
title, have played in the final in three of the IPL’s four
seasons.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  